description:
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to offer an opportunity to a committed pharmacist to work within our mental health services in Wigan. We are looking for a pharmacist who have extensive experience in mental health and are a qualified non-medical prescribers or who are currently undertaking non-medical prescribing training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working as a non-medical prescriber in as part of the Wigan South Recovery and SDF Team. This is ideal for a pharmacist, who is keen to develop the role of pharmacist within in the Trust and provide a high quality service to our service users. You will work closely with the South Team integrating with specialist to provide excellent medicines optimisation to our service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our friendly team provides an environment that encourages all staff to develop both the service and themselves.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant(s) will&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work within a locality mental health team and medicines management team to contribute to delivery of local &amp; Trust objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide specialist mental health advice across a diverse population with complex psychiatric needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide face to face medication reviews working as part of a wider multi-disciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a part of the innovative NWBH medicines management team benefiting from teaching, education and clinical supervision opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a pharmacist who has well-developed clinical and communication skills and a passion for delivering excellent care to our service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer flexible working hours and are committed to enabling good work/life balance for our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team provides remote out of hours advice only ‘on call’ services and the successful candidate will be required to be scheduled on an approximately 1 in 20 rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a medicines management role and there is no dispensary commitment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is subject to an enhanced check with adults barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is £47.50, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBarry RobertsonEmail addressBarry.Robertson@nwbh.nhs.ukTelephone number07917 556074&lt;/p&gt;
